UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 149/GA
1 AN ACT relating to the office of county treasurer.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 68.010 is amended to read as follows:
4 Notwithstanding the provisions of KRS 67.710, or any other statute:
5 (1) (a) The fiscal court of each county, by June 30 every four (4) years[, beginning
6 with June, 1999], shall appoint a county treasurer for a term of four (4) years
7 beginning on July 1 following the election held pursuant to Section 99 of
8 the Kentucky Constitution.
9 (b) [In 1998, the fiscal court of each county, by June 30, shall appoint a county
10 treasurer for a term of one (1) year. In 1999 and every four (4) years
11 thereafter, the fiscal court of each county shall appoint a county treasurer for a
12 term of four (4) years pursuant to paragraph (a) of this subsection.
13 (c) ]If for any reason the county treasurer is not appointed at the regular June
14 meeting, the county judge/executive shall call the fiscal court to meet on a day
15 fixed by order entered on the order book of the court, and the meeting shall be
16 held before the end of June.
17 (2) [The county treasurer shall take office on the July 1st immediately following his
18 appointment.
19 (3) ]No person is eligible to be county treasurer unless at the time of[ his] appointment
20 he or she is a citizen of Kentucky, is at least twenty-five (25) years old or has
21 obtained a baccalaureate level degree from a regionally accredited institution of
22 higher education. The county treasurer shall take the constitutional oath of office
23 before the fiscal court, and shall execute bond with an incorporated surety
24 company authorized and qualified to become surety on bonds in this state[at least
25 two (2) reputable sureties, to be approved by the fiscal court]. The fiscal court may
26 pay the premium on the bond from county funds.
27 (3)[(4)] If, at any time, the county treasurer is unable to perform the duties of this
Page 1 of 3
