UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 149/GA
1 office because of illness, physical or mental incapacity, absence, or other cause
2 beyond his or her control for more than five (5)[thirty (30)] days, or if there is a
3 vacancy created in the office by the resignation, termination, or death of the current
4 county treasurer, then the fiscal court may[shall] appoint, at either a regular term or
5 a special term called by the county judge/executive, an acting county treasurer to
6 serve until the current county treasurer is able to resume the performance of his or
7 her duties, or in the case of the resignation, termination, or death of the treasurer,
8 for a period not to exceed sixty (60) days, or until the end of the current county
9 treasurer's term of office, whichever comes first. Upon the conclusion of the sixty
10 (60) day acting county treasurer period, or at any time during that period if the
11 term of office has not ended, the fiscal court shall appoint a county treasurer to
12 serve the remainder of the term of office. Should the fiscal court be in doubt as to
13 the county treasurer's ability to resume his or her duties, it shall consult with a
14 licensed physician acceptable to both the fiscal court and the county treasurer. If the
15 physician advises that the county treasurer is able to perform his or her duties, the
16 county treasurer shall be reinstated within ten (10) days. As soon as the county
17 treasurer is reinstated, the acting county treasurer shall cease to act as county
18 treasurer and shall turn over to the county judge/executive all records and accounts
19 and shall make a final settlement with the fiscal court within thirty (30) days. The
20 fiscal court may remove the county treasurer or acting county treasurer at any time
21 for neglect of duty, incompetency, or dishonesty.
22 (4) The fiscal court of any county may appoint a deputy county treasurer who shall
23 serve at the fiscal court's pleasure under the supervision of the county treasurer.
24 The deputy county treasurer may exercise all powers, duties, and responsibilities
25 of the office of county treasurer subject to any restrictions imposed by the fiscal
26 court. The deputy county treasurer may serve as acting county treasurer under
27 subsection (3) of this section. The deputy county treasurer shall take the
